race.comment: SUMMER QUINN (7) finished well back at Wentworth Park last time when a 4.5 lengths fifth (29.91) but recorded best time of the card when winning four back. Strong form has emerged from her last run. Rates on top in this line up. ZIPPING CHETTY (8) was beaten for speed from wide out but attacked the line strongly to place, 2.5 lengths from the winner (29.78) at Wentworth Park in NG. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Leading chance. REBORN HOSTILITY (1) scored (34.77) last time out at Gosford in a Grade 5 and will break from box 1 for the first time. Has a good record here including three wins. Recorded the quickest time on the card last start. Can go close again if runs up to latest figure. ZIPPING BOTHAM (3) will be hard to beat despite making his debut at this trip.
